<!-- ================= DESCRIPTION ================= -->
<section class="container section-space">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-md-10" data-aos="fade-up">
            <div class="info-card">
                <h2>Architectural Significance</h2>
                <p class="mt-3">
                    The Paththirippuwa is one of the most symbolically powerful structures in Kandy,
                    representing royal authority, sacred hierarchy, and architectural control.
                    Designed by Devendra Mulachari during the Kandyan period, the structure combines
                    brick, lime mortar, timber, and tiled roofing to create a monumental yet culturally
                    restrained form.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Its elevated position and material strength established it as a visual and
                    ideological boundary, leading to the unwritten height regulation that still governs
                    Kandy today. The Paththirippuwa therefore functions not only as architecture, but as
                    a tool of cultural dominance and otherness.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

